headline.main: DETOUR IS ORDERED; 'Precaution' Is Taken in View of Attitude of Italian Leaders NORWAY RETREAT HINTED Withdrawal' Trial Balloon Stirs Liberal Chief to Urge Parliament to 'Act'

lead_paragraph: LONDON, April 30--British merchant ships have been ordered to keep out of the Mediterranean, as they were in the opening days of the war, when it was half expected that Premier Mussolini would cast Italy's fate in with that of his Axis partner.
